Author
======

Xiang-jian Gou (xjgou@stu.sicau.edu.cn)

Introduction
============

'CorrectGMATA.pl' can correct the output of GMATA

Input
=====

you should provide a motif type and five files for input, including : 
    1. motif type (can also be any character)
    2. frg file   (GMATA output)
    3. emap file  (GMATA output)
    4. mk file    (GMATA output)
    5. genome file
    6. ssr file   (GMATA output)

Output
======

the output file is based on the 'ssr' file, but add 2 more columns, including :
    1. column 'old' : previous  marker class (value 'poly' = polymorphic, 'mono' = monomorphic)
    2. column 'new' : now(true) marker class (value 'poly' = polymorphic, 'mono' = monomorphic, 'be-filtered' = no target SSR in PCR product)
